               <birth when="1914">He was born at <placeName ref="Q257830"/>.</birth>
                  <floruit notBefore="1930" notAfter="1992">He was  the son of a renowned musician
                     and an acclaimed violinist, was a professional lawyer and followed his legal career 
                     until the end of his life. Parallel to this, he was passionately devoted to Amharic language
                     and literature in which he achieved a deepened proficiency at the school of Francesco Gallina and 
                     then he started to teaching in the Istituto Orientale of <placeName ref="Q257830"/>
                     where he was later to hold a chair of Gǝʿǝz language and literature. 
                     He was widely reputed on account of his noteworthy literary production on the Amharic language and literature. 
                     He edited and translated Amharic texts into Italian. </floruit>
